<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="199" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1577,2036]" pageId="12" pageNumber="199">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,382,1722,1748]" pageId="12" pageNumber="199">Measurements.</emphasis>
Total length: 14.7–17.2; head length: 1.8–1.9; head width: 3.1–3.3; pronotal length: 2.6–2.9; pronotal width: 9.0–10.2; scutellum length: 7.2–8.1; scutellum width: 5.0–5.7; abdominal width: 8.2–9.3; length of antennal segments. I: 0.9–1.0; II: 2.0–2.2; III: 1.2–1.5; IV: 4.7–5.0; V: missing.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="202" pageId="12" pageNumber="199" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1577,2036]" lastBlockId="15.[151,1437,151,645]" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="202" pageId="12" pageNumber="199">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1829,1855]" pageId="12" pageNumber="199">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Anterolateral margin of pronotum with solid black stripe along all its extension. Anterolateral margin punctured dorsally. Cicatrices of pronotum with black punctures delimiting anterior sulci (
<figureCitation box="[1201,1303,1866,1892]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[252,1337,194,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-23@30.[237,1350,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 19. Dorsal and ventral view. H. excavatus sp. n. A–B; H. flexuosus sp. n. C–D; H. nigrosinuatus sp. n. E–F; H. omegoides sp. n. G–H; H. pentagonalis sp. n. I–J; H. rugulosus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." pageId="12" pageNumber="199">Fig. 19C</figureCitation>
). Scutellum with anterior margin yellow (
<figureCitation box="[488,593,1902,1928]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[252,1337,194,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-23@30.[237,1350,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 19. Dorsal and ventral view. H. excavatus sp. n. A–B; H. flexuosus sp. n. C–D; H. nigrosinuatus sp. n. E–F; H. omegoides sp. n. G–H; H. pentagonalis sp. n. I–J; H. rugulosus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." pageId="12" pageNumber="199">Fig. 19C</figureCitation>
). Body ventrally with stripes dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[1082,1189,1902,1928]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[252,1337,194,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-23@30.[237,1350,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 19. Dorsal and ventral view. H. excavatus sp. n. A–B; H. flexuosus sp. n. C–D; H. nigrosinuatus sp. n. E–F; H. omegoides sp. n. G–H; H. pentagonalis sp. n. I–J; H. rugulosus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." pageId="12" pageNumber="199">Fig. 19D</figureCitation>
). Male genitalia (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[229,1360,193,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-23@14.[214,1373,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 8. Hypoxys flexuosus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="12" pageNumber="199">Fig. 8A–D</figureCitation>
). Pygophore with dorsal rim excavated (
<figureCitation box="[683,774,1938,1964]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[229,1360,193,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-23@14.[214,1373,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 8. Hypoxys flexuosus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="12" pageNumber="199">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
). Superior process of genital cup subrectangular with both ends rounded; close to dorsal rim; visible in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[825,952,1974,2000]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[229,1360,193,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-23@14.[214,1373,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 8. Hypoxys flexuosus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="12" pageNumber="199">Fig. 8A–C</figureCitation>
). Paramere sinuous, twisted; anterior lobe digitiform, dorsally projected (
<figureCitation box="[503,630,2010,2036]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[229,1360,193,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-23@14.[214,1373,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 8. Hypoxys flexuosus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="12" pageNumber="199">Fig. 8A–C</figureCitation>
); posterior lobe almost inconspicuous; stalk with inner face carinated, carina ending at the apex of anterior lobe (
<figureCitation box="[638,761,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[229,1360,193,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-23@14.[214,1373,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 8. Hypoxys flexuosus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="15" pageNumber="202">Fig. 8B–C</figureCitation>
). Proctiger with dorsolateral dense tufts of long setae separated by an almost glabrous broad bridge; posterior face somewhat swollen, barrel-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[1168,1293,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[229,1360,193,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-23@14.[214,1373,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 8. Hypoxys flexuosus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="15" pageNumber="202">Fig. 8A–D</figureCitation>
). Ventral rim median excavation in “V”; expansions well-developed, large, acuminated, surpassing level of posterolateral angles in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[338,430,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[229,1360,193,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-23@14.[214,1373,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 8. Hypoxys flexuosus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="15" pageNumber="202">Fig. 8D</figureCitation>
). Female genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[654,743,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[229,1360,193,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-23@14.[214,1373,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 8. Hypoxys flexuosus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="15" pageNumber="202">Fig. 8E</figureCitation>
). Valvifers 8 subtrapezoidal; posterior margin almost straight and sloping; inner angle rounded and projected over valvifers 9; inner margins dark with small, distal, bottle-shaped excavation. Valvulae 9 barely exposed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption pageId="13" pageNumber="200" startId="13.[151,250,1943,1967]" targetBox="[248,1339,193,1911]" targetPageId="13">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1943,2004]" pageId="13" pageNumber="200">
