<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="202" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,366,392]" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">Comments.</emphasis>
The male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[599,739,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flexuosus">
<emphasis box="[599,739,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">H. flexuosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1907" box="[870,992,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dolosus">
<emphasis box="[870,992,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">H. dolosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1907" box="[1050,1207,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eburatulus">
<emphasis box="[1050,1207,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">H. eburatulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Nunes, B. M. &amp; Campos, L. D. &amp; Mendonca, M. T. S. &amp; Cunha, E. V. P. &amp; Fernandes, J. A. M." box="[1223,1432,367,393]" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" pagination="401 - 441" refId="ref18209" refString="Nunes, B. M., Campos, L. D., Mendonca, M. T. S., Cunha, E. V. P. &amp; Fernandes, J. A. M. (2020) Revision of Hypoxys Amyot &amp; Serville, 1843 stat. rest. (Heteroptera Pentatomidae). Zootaxa, 4742 (3), 401 - 441. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4742.3.1" type="journal article" year="2020">
Nunes 
<emphasis box="[1306,1364,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[151,248,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1915,1939]" captionTargetBox="[161,1417,544,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-158@8.[151,1436,525,1892]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Hypoxys crassimarginatum sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="15" pageNumber="202">Figs. 4B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[260,294,402,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[237,1347,191,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-23@10.[219,1367,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Hypoxys cristatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="15" pageNumber="202">5B</figureCitation>
) because paramere has anterior lobe long and curved dorsally and posterior lobe not developed; superior process of genital cup squared; and posterior face of proctiger somewhat swollen (
<figureCitation box="[1112,1233,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[229,1360,193,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-23@14.[214,1373,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 8. Hypoxys flexuosus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="15" pageNumber="202">Fig. 8B–C</figureCitation>
). But 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[1298,1436,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flexuosus">
<emphasis box="[1298,1436,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">H. flexuosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ from both by paramere twisted and superior process of genital cup subrectangular (
<figureCitation box="[1149,1270,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[229,1360,193,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-23@14.[214,1373,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 8. Hypoxys flexuosus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="15" pageNumber="202">Fig. 8B–C</figureCitation>
). Female genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[236,373,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flexuosus">
<emphasis box="[236,373,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">H. flexuosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, on the other hand, is not similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1907" box="[774,894,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dolosus">
<emphasis box="[774,894,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">H. dolosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1907" box="[930,1083,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eburatulus">
<emphasis box="[930,1083,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">H. eburatulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[1251,1395,511,536]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="excavatus">
<emphasis box="[1251,1395,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">H. excavatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1904" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boerneri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">H. boerneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and other species with valvifers 8 with medial excavation elliptical (
<figureCitation box="[1019,1115,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[229,1360,193,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-23@14.[214,1373,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 8. Hypoxys flexuosus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="15" pageNumber="202">Figs. 8E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1127,1162,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[248,1339,193,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-20@13.[228,1359,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 7. Hypoxys excavatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="15" pageNumber="202">7E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1065,583,609]" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,151,645]" box="[199,1065,583,609]" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,583,609]" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">Etymology.</emphasis>
Name refers to the sinuous parameres (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[779,883,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flexuosus">
<emphasis box="[779,883,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">flexuosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
=full of bends).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,787,618,645]" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,151,645]" box="[199,787,618,645]" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,618,644]" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">Distribution</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[361,465,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="32.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[203,1384,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-23@32.[203,1384,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURE 21. Distributional map of the new species of the H. quadridens group." pageId="15" pageNumber="202">Fig. 21A</figureCitation>
). 
<collectingCountry box="[485,561,619,645]" name="Peru" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">PERU</collectingCountry>
: Iquitos, 
<collectingRegion box="[661,783,619,645]" country="Peru" name="Amazonas" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">Amazonas</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
